[h3 id=AboutTheGame 
	" About the game
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Blood Omen: Legacy of Kain is an action-adventure game with similarities with Zelda games, but with a much darker story, and the first game of the Legacy of Kain series.
	$LF
	"The game only has few random elements, and as such most screens can easily be hex-edited. However the loading time between each screens is inconsistent. It runs at 60 FPS.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=Comments 
	" Comments
	$LF
]h3
[h4 id=VersionsDifferences 
	" Versions differences
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"For once the PSX version is faster than the PC one because the wrong warp used in this run doesn't work on the PC version. The loading times on PSX are longer though.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=MovementAndWeapons 
	" Movement and weapons
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Kain can move in 8 different directions.
	$LF
	"Vampire Kain runs at 540 unis per frame (256 units = 1 pixel), Wolf Kain runs at 1080 units per frame.
	$LF
	"Wolf Kain can also jump (for example over low level waters to not take damage), which is at least 17 frames slower than running.
	$LF
	"Taking damage push you in one direction for a few frames at double the speed, which can save up to 6 frames per damage boost.
	$LF
]div
